markdown <<MARKDOWN
# Why This Learning Approach is Critical

#### Programming with Music Lab is a fun and engaging unit of curriculum designed to teach students about core coding concepts while integrating the joy of making music. This curriculum is part of <a href="https://code.org/curriculum/csd" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Code.org's CS Discoveries curriculum</a>, but you do not need to teach any other unit within CS Discoveries to teach Programming with Music Lab.

<div style="margin: 20px auto">
<a class="btn btn-large btn-primary" href="https://studio.code.org/courses/programming-with-music-lab-2025/" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Programming with Music Lab Curriculum</a>
</div>

## Do I need to know about music to teach this curriculum?

<img src="https://images.code.org/66a965a55ff9dbc21f54c9b0aa258b61-image-1744140812694.28.33 PM.png" 
     alt="" 
     style="width: 20%; border-radius: 10px; margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px; float: right;">
     
#### Nope! Programming with Music Lab is designed to primarily teach about computer science. No learning outcomes are measured by the musicality of students' outputs (e.g. how "good" their songs sound). 

#### Instead, we focus on students' ability to write and revise code that showcases their knowledge about sequencing, loops, and functions. Any knowledge about music is a bonus, but certainly not required!

<p style="font-size: 18px; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #048899; margin: 20px 0px">If you find yourself wanting support with musical vocabulary, please access our <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1wvllTFs0IBWJI8uzfUhuFW4mUYItUK5nmmVjArNRlCM/edit?usp=sharing" target="blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Musical Terms Glossary</a>, which includes definitions and explanations to support instruction.
</p>


## Quick Facts About the Curriculum
